{"id":1221548414,"created_at":"2022-04-29T21:13:21Z","updated_at":"2022-05-03T16:02:46Z","state":"closed","title":"8265360: several compiler/whitebox tests fail with \"private compiler.whitebox.SimpleTestCaseHelper(int) must be compiled\"","html_url":"https://github.com/openjdk/jdk/pull/8473","body":"The compilation policy uses the length of the queues as a feedback mechanism that gives us information about the compilation speed. In some places it makes decisions based on the queue length length alone without looking at the invocation counters. That can cause a starvation effect. For example when running in a C2-only mode it may delay profiling in the interpreter if the C2 queue is too long. The solution to this is detect \"old\" methods (that is method that have been used a lot) and force putting them into the queue and let the queue prioritization deal with it.\r\n\r\nI also did some cleanup for things that got in the way.\r\nTesting looks clean.\n\n<!-- Anything below this marker will be automatically updated, please do not edit manually! -->\n---------\n### Progress\n- [x] Change must not contain extraneous whitespace\n- [x] Commit message must refer to an issue\n- [x] Change must be properly reviewed\n\n### Issue\n * [JDK-8265360](https://bugs.openjdk.java.net/browse/JDK-8265360): several compiler/whitebox tests fail with \"private compiler.whitebox.SimpleTestCaseHelper(int) must be compiled\"\n\n\n### Reviewers\n * [Vladimir Kozlov](https://openjdk.java.net/census#kvn) (@vnkozlov - **Reviewer**)\n * [Tobias Hartmann](https://openjdk.java.net/census#thartmann) (@TobiHartmann - **Reviewer**)\n\n\n### Reviewing\n<details><summary>Using <code>git<\/code><\/summary>\n\nCheckout this PR locally: \\\n`$ git fetch https://git.openjdk.java.net/jdk pull/8473/head:pull/8473` \\\n`$ git checkout pull/8473`\n\nUpdate a local copy of the PR: \\\n`$ git checkout pull/8473` \\\n`$ git pull https://git.openjdk.java.net/jdk pull/8473/head`\n\n<\/details>\n<details><summary>Using Skara CLI tools<\/summary>\n\nCheckout this PR locally: \\\n`$ git pr checkout 8473`\n\nView PR using the GUI difftool: \\\n`$ git pr show -t 8473`\n\n<\/details>\n<details><summary>Using diff file<\/summary>\n\nDownload this PR as a diff file: \\\n<a href=\"https://git.openjdk.java.net/jdk/pull/8473.diff\">https://git.openjdk.java.net/jdk/pull/8473.diff<\/a>\n\n<\/details>\n"}
{"id":1203246428,"created_at":"2022-04-13T12:39:59Z","updated_at":"2022-04-16T05:57:22Z","state":"closed","title":"8284681: compiler/c2/aarch64/TestFarJump.java fails with \"RuntimeException: for CodeHeap < 250MB the far jump is expected to be encoded with a single branch instruction\"","html_url":"https://github.com/openjdk/jdk/pull/8223","body":"Recently [introduced](https://bugs.openjdk.java.net/browse/JDK-8280872) TestFarJump.java test checks the PrintAssembly output for ADRP instruction. Test fails intermittently when the subsequent raw address is similar to the ADRP instruction encoding. With this fix, the test is fixed to only check the first instruction of the exception handler to avoid false positives.\r\n\r\nFalse positive case, the raw pointer is disassembled as ADRP instruction:\r\n```\r\n[Exception Handler]\r\n  0x0000fffdd3940410: ; {runtime_call handle_exception_from_callee Runtime1 stub}\r\n  0x0000fffdd3940410: 5c50 8695 | c1d5 bbd4 | 78be 56f0 | fdff 0000 \r\n\r\nDisassembly:\r\n0x0000000000000000:  5C 50 86 95    bl    #0x6194170\r\n0x0000000000000004:  C1 D5 BB D4    dcps1 #0xdeae\r\n0x0000000000000008:  78 BE 56 F0    adrp  x24, #0xad7cf000\r\n0x000000000000000c:  FC FF 00 00    n/a\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe row pointer (above) is pointer to \"should not reach here\" chars:\r\n```cpp\r\nvoid MacroAssembler::stop(const char* msg) {\r\n  BLOCK_COMMENT(msg);\r\n  dcps1(0xdeae);\r\n  emit_int64((uintptr_t)msg);\r\n}\r\n\r\nvoid should_not_reach_here() { stop(\"should not reach here\"); }\r\n\r\nint LIR_Assembler::emit_exception_handler() {\r\n  ...\r\n  __ far_call(RuntimeAddress(Runtime1::entry_for(Runtime1::handle_exception_from_callee_id)));  \r\n  __ should_not_reach_here();\r\n}\r\n```\n\n<!-- Anything below this marker will be automatically updated, please do not edit manually! -->\n---------\n### Progress\n- [x] Change must not contain extraneous whitespace\n- [x] Commit message must refer to an issue\n- [x] Change must be properly reviewed\n\n### Issue\n * [JDK-8284681](https://bugs.openjdk.java.net/browse/JDK-8284681): compiler/c2/aarch64/TestFarJump.java fails with \"RuntimeException: for CodeHeap < 250MB the far jump is expected to be encoded with a single branch instruction\"\n\n\n### Reviewers\n * [Vladimir Kozlov](https://openjdk.java.net/census#kvn) (@vnkozlov - **Reviewer**)\n\n\n### Reviewing\n<details><summary>Using <code>git<\/code><\/summary>\n\nCheckout this PR locally: \\\n`$ git fetch https://git.openjdk.java.net/jdk pull/8223/head:pull/8223` \\\n`$ git checkout pull/8223`\n\nUpdate a local copy of the PR: \\\n`$ git checkout pull/8223` \\\n`$ git pull https://git.openjdk.java.net/jdk pull/8223/head`\n\n<\/details>\n<details><summary>Using Skara CLI tools<\/summary>\n\nCheckout this PR locally: \\\n`$ git pr checkout 8223`\n\nView PR using the GUI difftool: \\\n`$ git pr show -t 8223`\n\n<\/details>\n<details><summary>Using diff file<\/summary>\n\nDownload this PR as a diff file: \\\n<a href=\"https://git.openjdk.java.net/jdk/pull/8223.diff\">https://git.openjdk.java.net/jdk/pull/8223.diff<\/a>\n\n<\/details>\n"}
